in the country. Soon enough, the little scenes such as rading the accused drug dealers and users and demolish their houses afterwards were a part of the film. This was something i would never forget because Hendrix\'s brother-in-law suddenly forces him to pee in a plastic because the police were about to rade them. Next thing he knows, his sister and his brother in law panics and he accidentally touches the poop in the plastic he was holding- Yuck!\r\n\r\n<strong><b>Revolves around the rap culture.</b></strong>\r\n\r\nOf course, the life inside and outside of rapping was the focus on most of the scenes the film. It gave me an impression that Flip Top is no game and a hobby of wanna-be hip-hop Filipino groups is an art form that entails practice, word power, and excellence. The approach of adding a veteran poet in the character made the film much more interesting because I was able to compare and contrast rapping in the modern era and the classics of <em><i>pakikipagbalagtasan </i></em>in other words poetic competition.\r\n\r\nThese are only a few things that I have noticed in the film and are the causes of which I never thought would make me view Flip Top in a different way. It has made me become more open with what I think is <em><i>baduy </i></em>and has changed my perspective in the different art forms of rap battle.', 'Respeto as an Eyeopener', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-03-16 01:04:53', '2018-03-16 05:04:53', '', 60, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/2018/03/16/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(63, 1, '2018-03-16 01:06:10', '2018-03-16 05:06:10', 'The harsh reality of what we call \"poverty- pornographic\" about Eduardo Roy Jr.\'s Pamilya Ordinaryo was a vivid representation that was meticulously written and produced. Think of it this way: Two kids living in the streets of Manila have themselves a new-born baby, gets stolen by a seemingly generous male cross dresser and searches for their missing child. Through the journey, they experience disgusting maltreatment from the police (who should be the first ones to help them), criminal acts, a news feature, and false hopes.\r\n\r\nFor those individuals who are afraid to experience first hand or even witness minors doing drugs, stealing, robbing, and cursing as their language in locations such as marketplaces, street corners, tunnels and bridges- this is not at all an imagination and is a nightmare to passersby.\r\n\r\nWhat is oddly interesting is that, while this is the continuous issue running in the country, it is still unrecognized and shrugged off by the people of who can help prevent these unfortunate events. The film added the CCTV footages as a tool to depict the reality of which we ourselves may be unaware of and is already happening. The power of the film being able to shamelessly let its audience feel disturbed is very effective.\r\n\r\nThe starring couple, Jane and Aries is presented as a very mischievous duo. To survive a day they have no choice but to do reckless activities such as pickpocketing, having sex, screaming, sleeping, fighting but despite of it all, they are each other\'s strong foundation and manage to deal with each other as family. The scenes in the film produced a number of metaphors that is timely to the social and economic situation of the Philippines under the brackets C and D.\r\n\r\nThroughout the long feature- and aside from the vulgar scenes about hypocrisy, unjust and abusive social and governmental institutions that supposedly help and protect the poor and the oppressed, the couple have been the main focus of the evidences of these truths because as hard and difficult as it is to digest the story, it is always a taboo that we wish we could change.\r\n\r\nFor someone who has only started watching Cinemalaya films for only 3 years and counting, this is the only film that has been very moving and has achieved to raise- consciousness to the Filipino audience. The vulgar representation of what the title means by Pamilya Ordinaryo depicts an ironic theme due to the several consecutive unfortunate events that had happened to the starring couple. The disheartening realization after viewing the film is how society do not give so much importance to the point wherein it has become the biggest taboo in the country, which makes it a spectacular- touching film.\r\n\r\nThe reason behind a great admiration for the film is that it showed a very authentic and raw situation of the life of poor teenage parents who were victimized by their family, agents of the police, media, local government, heartless pranksters. There were various scenes that made the audiences react so violently that is enough proof that Pamilya Ordinaryo was well deserving of its claimed awards by many competitions.', 'Nothing Ordinary in Pamilya Ordinaryo', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nothing-ordinary-in-pamilya-ordinaryo', '', '', '2018-03-20 10:40:12', '2018-03-20 14:40:12', '', 0, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/?p=63', 0, 'post', '', 0),
