(78, 1, '2018-03-16 01:14:24', '2018-03-16 05:14:24', 'Cinemalaya is known to welcome entries that the objectives are to raise awareness of social issue relevance, highlight the political injustice present in the society and jar away from the typical mainstream movies that are popularly shown in the country. As someone who is not a fan of supporting mainstream Filipino movies, the expectations I have for Cinemalaya is quite high. Knowing that filmmakers are free to submit what they have to offer, I\'m very much pleased with seeing the LGBT community be a part of the characters. One of the films I have watched from Cinemalaya is entitled <em><i>Ang Pagdadalaga ni Maximo Oliveros, </i></em>which was directed by Auraeus Solito. The movie starred a 12-year-old boy named Maxi. Coming from the title, it is about the coming of age of a homosexual boy. The story revolved around how Maxi\'s family, his social status and his attitude towards whatever situation he is faced. There are a lot of films that were shown in Cinemalaya that are about Homosexuality. In fact, they populate almost all of the influential personalities in the country. These are Vice Ganda, BJ Pascual, Congresswoman Geraldine Roman and Rajo Laurel. As you might not have noticed, the ones that are mentioned are only those who are gay and transgender women. The representation and the acceptance of lesbians in country are not very popular. There are actually a lot of misconceptions about the lesbian community. One of its stereotypes is that a lesbian automatically wants to look like a boy, act like a boy and talk like a boy. Yes, the LGBT community is accepted in the country thus films like Ang Pagdadalaga ni Maximo Oliveros but it\'s quite unfortunate that there aren\'t a lot of lesbian characters in Cinemalaya not as quite often as gay characters. I guess how I view the diverse genre entries of Cinemalaya is that it still needs more representations of other groups in the society.', 'A Different View On The LGBT Cinemalaya Films', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-different-view-on-the-lgbt-cinemalaya-films', '', '', '2018-03-20 10:41:27', '2018-03-20 14:41:27', '', 0, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/?p=78', 0, 'post', '', 0),
