(99, 1, '2018-03-19 08:23:25', '2018-03-19 12:23:25', '<style>.entry-header{display: none;}</style>\r\n<div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-3\"><img src=\"http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/1212.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-9\"><strong style=\"font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; display: block; font-family: bebas;\">Mark Meily</strong>Mark is a multi-awarded filmmaker. He is the director of Donor (2010) in Cinemalaya Independent Film Festival. He won the award for Best Cinematography for his film. His feature films have been presented at the film festivals of Deauville, Hawaii, Seattle, Goteborg, Marrakech, Montreal, Busan, Fukuoka and Brussels.\r\nMark is also a film educator.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-3\"><img src=\"http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/1213.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-9\"><strong style=\"font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; display: block; font-family: bebas;\">Dennis Marasigan</strong>Dennis is an actor, writer, filmmaker and producer. He started acting in theater and later on worked in the film industry. Dennis submitted two (2) films in Cinemalaya entitled, “Vox Populi” (2010) and “Tukso” (2007). He is the director of Tukso which has won the award for Best Screenplay in the year 2007 in Cinemalaya Independent Film Festival.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-3\"><img src=\"http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/1214.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-9\"><strong style=\"font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; display: block; font-family: bebas;\">Adriana Agcaoili</strong>Adriana is writer, host and theater and film actor. She was involved in Cinemalaya in 2009 as an actress in Mike Sandejas’ film “Dinig Sana Kita”. The film went on to win these awards in the festival: Audience’s Choice and Balanghai Trophy for Best Musical Score, National Council for Children’s Television Award, as well as the Star Award for New Movie Actor of the Year for the male lead, Romalito Mallari, a real hearing-impaired dancer and actor, and was a Gawad Urian nominee for Best Music. In 2013, she was the Awards Night event writer.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-3\"><img src=\"http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/1215.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-9\"><strong style=\"font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; display: block; font-family:bebas;\">Franz Valenzuela</strong>Franz is an amateur filmmaker and a Cinemalaya enthusiast since 2007. She has finished a Bachelor’s Degree on Media Production. She has exprienced directing short films when she was in college. In the year 2017, Franz has received the award for Best Cinematography in her college for her short film entitled “Check-In”. Currently, she is based in New York City to pursue her filmmaking career.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-3\"><img src=\"http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/1216.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-9\"><strong style=\"font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; display: block; font-family: bebas;\">Gia Gumisad</strong>Gia is currently taking Communications in college. She is a Cinemalaya Enthusiats since 2014. Often times, she would write reviews on the Cinemalaya films that she has watched. Gia has also took up Theater Arts in University of the Philippines - Diliman. She has a lot of experience when it comes to theater acting, hosting, and performing.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'The Contributors', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-contributors', '', '', '2018-03-20 16:15:28', '2018-03-20 20:15:28', '', 0, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/?page_id=99', 0, 'page', '', 0),
