Musical Score, National Council for Children’s Television Award, as well as the Star Award for New Movie Actor of the Year for the male lead, Romalito Mallari, a real hearing-impaired dancer and actor, and was a Gawad Urian nominee for Best Music. In 2013, she was the Awards Night event writer.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-3\"><img src=\"http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/1215.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-9\"><strong style=\"font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; display: block;\">Franz Valenzuela</strong>Franz is an amateur filmmaker and a Cinemalaya enthusiast since 2007. She has finished a Bachelor’s Degree on Media Production. She has exprienced directing short films when she was in college. In the year 2017, Franz has received the award for Best Cinematography in her college for her short film entitled “Check-In”. Currently, she is based in New York City to pursue her filmmaking career.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-bottom: 30px\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-3\"><img src=\"http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/1216.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-9\"><strong style=\"font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 15px; display: block;\">Gia Gumisad</strong>Gia is currently taking Communications in college. She is a Cinemalaya Enthusiats since 2014. Often times, she would write reviews on the Cinemalaya films that she has watched. Gia has also took up Theater Arts in University of the Philippines - Diliman. She has a lot of experience when it comes to theater acting, hosting, and performing.\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'The Contributors', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '99-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-03-19 08:38:50', '2018-03-19 12:38:50', '', 99, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/article/99-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(116, 1, '2018-03-19 08:40:26', '2018-03-19 12:40:26', '<style>.entry-header {display: none;}</style>\r\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 2.75rem; font-family: Montserrat, \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif;     font-weight: 700;\r\n    line-height: 1.25;\"><center><strong>Advertising Policy</strong></center></h1>\r\nThe views and opinions written by contributors and images utilized in the E-magazine entitled “Through The Eyes” do not necessarily reflect or represent the views of the proponent. “Through The Eyes” E-magazine and its contributors are not associated, connected nor affiliated with Cinemalaya Film Festival organizers and do not reflect or represent the said entity. For clarifications, this medium is for the soul purpose of only an academic requirement. The articles that are included in this medium may contain content copyrighted by another entity or person. It involves the given permission of each contributor by expressing their own personal point of view of the Cinemalaya Film Festival and wishes to promote the films that are locally made and produced. \r\n\r\nThe contents of this E- Magazine is limited and shall not be limited to: Informing the youth of the social relevance of the articles, Spreading awareness to the youth about societal issues represented by the films, and encouraging the youth to support Cinemalaya films presented available only in the Philippines. The stated objectives are only the ideal goal of the editor but does not confirm that this E- Magazine is a promotional material of the Cinemalaya Film Festival. This E-Magazine targets Male and Female ages 18 to 25 years old, preferably those who are in High School, College, Aspiring Filmmakers and individuals who are a part of the film and art industry. \r\n\r\nThe contents of the material do not impose on any insult directed to whatever is stated but are just subjective opinions by the writer. The editor of this E-Magazine publishes what is ought to be given attention to in order to enlighten the readers. The interpretation by the reader of the articles may acquire contradicting views based on their own personal standing but are free to determine for themselves what to accept or reject. Moreover, the contents of this E-Magazine highlight each contributor\'s freedom of speech but do not accept any libelous statements in order to maintain professionalism in the material. Lastly, ethics and practicality are still present throughout the making of each article about how the writers are free of expressing their own thoughts, suggestions and opinions without shaming any third party for that matter.', 'Advertising Policy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'advertising-policy', '', '', '2018-03-20 10:08:43', '2018-03-20 14:08:43', '', 0, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/?page_id=116', 0, 'page', '', 0),
