(129, 1, '2018-03-19 09:03:35', '2018-03-19 13:03:35', 'The great thing about Cinemalaya Independent Film Festival for me is that it is the most honest film festival in the Philippines. It is honest in the sense that filmmakers do not produce Cinemalaya films in order to make so much money. All of the stories that were created are from the heart. Every filmmaker, whether they win or not, they fabricated a movie that is sincere and not just to win. I am glad because I have seen Cinemalaya from the very beginning. It started from a small-scale until it reached this year. Usually Cinemalaya Independent Film Festival is held during the month of August when the rain pours which results to the people not being able to support the screenings of the films nevertheless through the years.. 13 great years, Cinemalaya has become a major force. The fact that some independent filmmakers measure their success when they are already producing mainstream movies nonetheless maybe it’s really how careers go or history folds. There is nothing wrong with mainstream cinema but I hope that the filmmakers who have entered the industry could always go back to making independent films. The end goal is not producing a low budget film to receive an award, or for you to be well known nor to make so much money. I don’t think that should be the final purpose of any filmmaker. I’m glad that Cinemalaya Independent Film Festival has given their audience a choice wherein people can watch their films that were produced without pressure for commercial viability. ', 'Cinemalaya As The Most Honest Film Festival in the Philippines', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cinemalaya-as-the-most-honest-film-festival-in-the-philippines', '', '', '2018-03-20 10:41:45', '2018-03-20 14:41:45', '', 0, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/?p=129', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(130, 1, '2018-03-19 09:03:35', '2018-03-19 13:03:35', 'The great thing about Cinemalaya Independent Film Festival for me is that it is the most honest film festival in the Philippines. It is honest in the sense that filmmakers do not produce Cinemalaya films in order to make so much money. All of the stories that were created are from the heart. Every filmmaker, whether they win or not, they fabricated a movie that is sincere and not just to win. I am glad because I have seen Cinemalaya from the very beginning. It started from a small-scale until it reached this year. Usually Cinemalaya Independent Film Festival is held during the month of August when the rain pours which results to the people not being able to support the screenings of the films nevertheless through the years.. 13 great years, Cinemalaya has become a major force. The fact that some independent filmmakers measure their success when they are already producing mainstream movies nonetheless maybe it’s really how careers go or history folds. There is nothing wrong with mainstream cinema but I hope that the filmmakers who have entered the industry could always go back to making independent films. The end goal is not producing a low budget film to receive an award, or for you to be well known nor to make so much money. I don’t think that should be the final purpose of any filmmaker. I’m glad that Cinemalaya Independent Film Festival has given their audience a choice wherein people can watch their films that were produced without pressure for commercial viability. ', 'Cinemalaya As The Most Honest Film Festival in the Philippines', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '129-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-03-19 09:03:35', '2018-03-19 13:03:35', '', 129, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/article/129-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
