evelops into an ambiguous attraction. This being from the very first Cinemalaya film festival, was a brave move considering the social climate of the Philippines toward LGBT culture at the time. For many years, being “bakla” or “tomboy” in Philippine media would always have a comedic connotation - the overly rambunctious cross-dressing gay and the virgin tomboy awaiting a real man’s touch. And for many years, this form of “toleration” of the LGBT community was all the representation there was in Philippine society. But through films like this, the truth of the LGBT community’s story is brought out of the shadows and onto the silver screen for all to open their eyes. It is thanks to this movie that many more entries into the Cinemalaya film festival were able to be transparent about sexuality - a most taboo discussion for a traditionally Catholic country. Especially through the perspective of an innocent child just going through life, experiencing every “normal” encounter in a young person’s life - like a simple crush. This simply told story about a little crush will always represent the truth of humanity - no matter who we are and where we come from we all deserve to love.', 'How Brave, Maxi', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '132-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-03-19 09:06:15', '2018-03-19 13:06:15', '', 132, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/article/132-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(134, 1, '2018-03-19 09:25:22', '2018-03-19 13:25:22', '', 'Cinemalaya: Not Just a Festival but also a Movement', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', '__trashed', '', '', '2018-03-19 09:25:22', '2018-03-19 13:25:22', '', 0, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/?p=134', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(135, 1, '2018-03-19 09:07:20', '2018-03-19 13:07:20', 'In a country where Catholicism dominates, beliefs and values restrict one\'s ability to validate their sexuality. There are pros and cons in so many aspects of this norm and yet it is obvious that these affect how the society views the people who show their indifference from what is suppose to be accepted. \r\n\r\nWhen we talk about the specifics, majority of the Filipinos acknowledge the existence of the LGBT community however their actions and behavior do not reciprocate this. It may seem as if it is accepted just because many of the LGBT community already dominate certain fields but the discrimination and disgust is still present. As someone who sees the world in a totally different angle, which is at the losing end of the indiscretion happening in the society, it is unavoidable to feel outcasted and burdened. Furthermore, it hinders the LGBT group to be harmonious with the rest of the community. \r\n	\r\nThere are a number of people from the LGBT community who try to jar away from feeling secluded; they use many channels such as media to change the system. These brave souls use their intellect and capabilities for the society to be proven wrong. Nowadays, unjust treatment to the LGBT members are being noticed and are given attention to in such a way that more and more individuals are siding on them. \r\n	\r\nOne way of supporting this notion is featuring this topic in films. In Cinemalaya, the rainbow theme is becoming a trend to the industry. More directors and writers draw attention to the topic and make characters about it. FIlms such as Translacion: Ang Paglalakad sa Altar ng Alanganin, Ang Pagdadalaga ni Maximo Oliveros, Kasal, and many more. \r\n	\r\nIt relieves many Filipinos who are part of the LGBT population because it gives hope and recognition that these individuals are no different than the rest of the straight community. At the same time, it sends off a message that the artists are being part of a movement where these so called \"different\" people are welcome and should not be ashamed of who they are. It brings joy to those who hide in the shadows- afraid to be truly who they are. \r\n\r\nCinemalaya is indeed a very special medium to include everyone who is anyone and is a platform that stands for the people who cannot stand for themselves. \r\n', 'Cinemalaya: Not Just a Festival but also a Movement', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cinemalaya-not-just-a-festival-but-also-a-movement', '', '', '2018-03-27 21:54:56', '2018-03-28 01:54:56', '', 0, 'http://throughtheeyes.info/iteration1/?p=135', 0, 'post', '', 0),
